<TITLE> Envoys to India, US, UK to get state minister rank </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 28 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh's envoys to India and the United States and United Kingdom will now enjoy the status of state ministers, an adviser to the prime minister said on Wednesday. "The envoys of these three countries have been awarded the status of state minister at the directive of the prime minister," HT Imam told reporters after opening a workshop at Sheraton Hotel. Their status will not make any problem in state protocol, said Imam, who advises prime minister Sheikh Hasina on establishment and administration. He added a gazette notification will be issued soon. Akramul Qader is the ambassador to US, Sayedur Rahman Khan the high commissioner to UK while Ahmed Tariq Karim is the high commissioner to India. Imam said the three will work under the foreign ministry. The discipline in the administration will not be breached. The establishment ministry organised the workshop titled 'Vision, mission, values, roles and renaming of establishment ministry'. Establishment secretary Iqbal Mahmud and additional secretary Mohammad Sadique were among those who spoke. b
